ricing more hikes; fresh soft prints on both would flip further dovish.", "confidence": 0.45, "risks": [{"tag": "policy", "text": "Stale labor/inflation reads could already be stale wrong; a surprise print could jump the front end sharply."}, {"tag": "liquidity", "text": "Continued balance-sheet runoff could tighten front-end funding more than FC easing offsets."}, {"tag": "positioning", "text": "Position is small conviction; low liquidity in short bills could exaggerate slippage on rebalancing."}, {"tag": "carry", "text": "Flat-ish front-end trade earns little carry if the range persists through month end."}], "trade": {"legs": [{"instrument": "DGS1", "weight": 0.02}, {"instrument": "DGS3MO", "weight": -0.03}], "conviction": 0.15, "rationale": "Hold prior modest front-end position: slight steepening bias within 2y reflecting easing FC offset by balance-sheet-driven liquidity tightness; no driver turned enough to resize."}}

